Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mild normocytic, hypochromic anemia, thrombocytosis, impaired renal function (elevated creatinine), marked hyperbilirubinemia, mildly elevated ALT, and significant metabolic acidosis (low pH, low O2 saturation). Coagulation is slightly altered (low PT, high INR). Lipid profile is markedly abnormal (high total and LDL cholesterol). Findings suggest possible liver dysfunction, renal impairment, and increased cardiovascular risk. Immediate clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
